{
  "description": "The context management system in Flask is responsible for managing the application and request contexts. These contexts provide a way to access application-specific and request-specific data within view functions and other parts of the application. The system ensures that the necessary data is available when needed and cleaned up afterward, maintaining a clean and organized execution environment. The Flask application creates and manages both application and request contexts, pushing them onto a stack when they are active and popping them off when they are no longer needed. This mechanism allows Flask to maintain a clean and isolated execution environment for each request.",
